<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
For detailed morphology see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1347 - 1415" refId="B6" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Loebl, I, 1997. Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Journal of Natural History 31: 1347 - 1415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" title="Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" volume="31" year="1997">
Cuccodoro and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
. Combined length of head, pronotum, and elytra 1.6-1.9 mm; maximal pronotal width = 0.9-1.1 mm. Body and appendages (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 7–9" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 7 - 9. Megarthrus hemipterus (Illiger): habitus, male: dorsal 7 ventral 8 and lateral 9 views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures7-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578545" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">7-9</figureCitation>
) rust brown; head markedly darker with frons slightly paler than vertex. Anterior frontal margin slightly carinate, evenly convex in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures7-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578545" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figures 7–9" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Figures 7-9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1794" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus hemipterus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Illiger): habitus, male: dorsal 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">7</emphasis>
ventral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">8</emphasis>
and lateral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">9</emphasis>
views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Protibia fairly straight and slightly enlarged toward apex, evenly, with adventral side markedly depressed transversely at middle. Mesotrochanter with about a dozen of peg-like setae arranged in two rows. Mesofemur slightly arcuate and slightly swollen. Mesotibia subangulate, bearing peg-like setae arranged in one row. Metatrochanter and metafemur slightly swollen; posterior margin of metatrochanter evenly arcuate; inner margin of metafemur slightly concave in ventral view, forming sharp ridge on entire length. Metatibia swollen, at middle forming conspicuous tooth-like process projecting above flattened apical portion of metatibia; metatibial peg-like setae arranged in 1-2 rows on apical third, the latter group of 15-20, discontinuously with more than 12 peg-like setae arranged in two rows on distal side of tooth-like process; proximal side of tooth-like process broad and flat, bearing 4-10 scattered peg-like setae. Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">15</figureCitation>
) with ventral wall not narrowed at base and gradually narrowed to mucronate apex in ventral view, with ventral fairly straight to apex in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Gonocoxal plate with lateral portions of dorsobasal margin straight to middle portion forming small blunt process slightly projecting anterad. Dorsal part of genitalia with arcuate sclerite wider at middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figures 10–18" startId="F4">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Figures 10-18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus dentipes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus dentipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bernhauer (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">10, 13, 16</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. flavolimbatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="flavolimbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. flavolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cameron (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">11, 14, 17</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. hemipterus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Illiger) (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">12, 15, 18</emphasis>
) male: aedeagus in ventral (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">10-12</emphasis>
) and lateral (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">13-15</emphasis>
) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">16-18</emphasis>
) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
