<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution and natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1794" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus hemipterus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widespread member of the genus, with records ranging from the United Kingdom in the West to China, South Korea, Japan, and Far East Russia in the East (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79957" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="475 - 524" refId="B3" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 1996. Revision of the Japanese rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae). Revue suisse de Zoologie 103 (2): 475 - 524, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79957" title="Revision of the Japanese rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79957" volume="103" year="1996">Cuccodoro 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1347 - 1415" refId="B6" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Loebl, I, 1997. Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Journal of Natural History 31: 1347 - 1415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" title="Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" volume="31" year="1997">
Cuccodoro and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/n11-004" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="317 - 331" refId="B7" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Kim, HM, Ahn, KJ, 2011. Megarthrus of Korea, with description of a new species (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). The Canadian Entomologist 143: 317 - 331, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/n11-004" title="Megarthrus of Korea, with description of a new species (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/n11-004" volume="143" year="2011">Cuccodoro et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It occurs in a wide range of microhabitats (carrion, fungi, leaf litter, and various types of decaying organic matter); in South Korea it was abundantly collected from fresh and rotten fungi. The first record for China without precise locality data (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1347 - 1415" refId="B6" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Loebl, I, 1997. Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Journal of Natural History 31: 1347 - 1415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" title="Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" volume="31" year="1997">
Cuccodoro and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
